---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Button from "@components/atoms/Button.astro";
import DSAIBlock from "@components/sections/DSAIBlock.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About LBS AI Lab"
  description="LBS AI Lab teaches London Business School students to build AI products, test with real users, and iterate from feedback."
>
  <section class="about-hero">
    <div class="container hero-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">About LBS AI Lab</p>
        <h1>Building is easier now. Users are the hard part.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          AI-assisted coding has made it possible to move from idea to prototype
          quickly. The Lab teaches the harder skill: choosing a real problem,
          testing with real LBS users, and improving until the product becomes
          useful.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <Button href="/apply/" variant="red" size="lg"
            >Register interest</Button
          >
          <Button href="/cohorts/cohort-01/" variant="ghost" size="lg"
            >See Cohort 01</Button
          >
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="hero-note" aria-label="Lab thesis">
        <span>The Lab model</span>
        <ol>
          <li>Learn the modern AI build stack.</li>
          <li>Build for an LBS use case.</li>
          <li>Test with students, alumni, and operators.</li>
          <li>Iterate from evidence, not opinion.</li>
        </ol>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section thesis-section">
    <div class="container thesis-grid">
      <div class="rule" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Why it exists</p>
        <h2>The bottleneck moved from building to learning.</h2>
        <p>
          Vibe coding, agentic engineering, and automation have compressed the
          cost of making software. That changes what students need to learn. The
          question is no longer only “can we build it?” It is “can we find the
          right users, understand the real workflow, and keep improving?”
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-cloud audience-section">
    <div class="container audience-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">What makes it different</p>
        <h2>The audience is built into the Lab.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="audience-copy">
        <p>
          Every Lab project starts with an LBS use case. That gives teams access
          to the thing most builders struggle to get: real people who can use,
          reject, critique, and shape the product.
        </p>
        <dl>
          <div>
            <dt>2,000+</dt>
            <dd>LBS students to learn from</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Alumni</dt>
            <dd>A global network for feedback and expertise</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Live workflows</dt>
            <dd>Careers, clubs, learning, funding, campus, and work</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section how-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-intro">
        <p class="eyebrow">How the Lab works</p>
        <h2>A practical loop, taught by doing.</h2>
        <p>
          The Lab is cohort-based, mentor-supported, and built around shipping.
          Students learn by moving through the same product loop they will use
          as founders, operators, and product builders.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="process-list">
        <article>
          <span>01</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Choose a real LBS workflow</h3>
            <p>
              Start with a visible problem in student life, alumni life, campus
              operations, recruiting, learning, funding, or professional work.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>02</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Build quickly with AI-assisted tools</h3>
            <p>
              Use agentic engineering, automation, and product judgement to move
              from idea to working prototype without waiting months.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>03</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Put it in front of users</h3>
            <p>
              Test with people who feel the problem now. Watch what they do,
              listen to what they say, and separate signal from politeness.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>04</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Improve and show the work</h3>
            <p>
              Iterate from feedback, sharpen the product, and demo what changed
              because of real user evidence.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-warm outcomes-section">
    <div class="container outcomes-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">What students learn</p>
        <h2>Not just how to prompt. How to build.</h2>
      </div>
      <ul>
        <li>How to turn a messy workflow into a clear product scope.</li>
        <li>How to use AI tools to build faster without losing judgement.</li>
        <li>How to recruit early users and interpret feedback honestly.</li>
        <li>How to keep shipping when the first version is not right.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <DSAIBlock />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    background: var(--color-lbs-blue);
    color: var(--color-white);
    padding-block: clamp(56px, 7vw, 96px);
  }

  .hero-grid {
    align-items: center;
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(32px, 6vw, 76px);
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(300px, 0.42fr);
  }

  .hero-grid > * {
    min-width: 0;
  }

  :global(.about-hero .eyebrow) {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.82);
  }

  h1 {
    color: var(--color-white);
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 5.4vw, 4.8rem);
    margin: 18px 0;
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  .lede {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    max-width: 780px;
  }

  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-top: 28px;
  }

  .hero-note {
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-lbs-red);
    display: grid;
    gap: 18px;
    padding-left: clamp(20px, 3vw, 30px);
  }

  .hero-note span {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.62);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    font-weight: 880;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .hero-note ol {
    counter-reset: item;
    display: grid;
    gap: 14px;
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .hero-note li {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.84);
    font-size: var(--step-0);
    font-weight: 760;
    line-height: 1.35;
  }

  .thesis-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(28px, 6vw, 74px);
    grid-template-columns: minmax(4px, 0.13fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
  }

  .rule {
    background: var(--color-lbs-red);
    min-height: 100%;
    width: 4px;
  }

  .thesis-grid h2,
  .audience-grid h2,
  .section-intro h2,
  .outcomes-grid h2 {
    color: var(--color-lbs-blue);
    margin: 16px 0;
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  .thesis-grid p:not(.eyebrow),
  .audience-copy p,
  .section-intro p:not(.eyebrow) {
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    font-size: var(--step-1);
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  .audience-grid,
  .outcomes-grid {
    align-items: start;
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(28px, 6vw, 74px);
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.62fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
  }

  .audience-copy {
    display: grid;
    gap: 30px;
  }

  dl {
    border-block: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    margin: 0;
  }

  dl div {
    border-left: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: 18px;
  }

  dl div:first-child {
    border-left: 0;
  }

  dt {
    color: var(--color-lbs-blue);
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--step-2);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  dd {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-weight: 780;
    line-height: 1.25;
    margin: 9px 0 0;
  }

  .section-intro {
    max-width: 860px;
  }

  .process-list {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin-top: 42px;
  }

  .process-list article {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(18px, 4vw, 46px);
    grid-template-columns: 80px minmax(0, 1fr);
    padding-block: clamp(22px, 4vw, 34px);
  }

  .process-list span {
    color: var(--color-lbs-red);
    font-weight: 900;
  }

  .process-list h3 {
    color: var(--color-lbs-blue);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--step-1);
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 8px;
  }

  .process-list p {
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    max-width: 820px;
  }

  .outcomes-grid ul {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0;
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .outcomes-grid li {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    font-size: var(--step-1);
    font-weight: 720;
    line-height: 1.35;
    padding-block: 18px;
  }

  .outcomes-grid li:last-child {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .hero-grid,
    .audience-grid,
    .outcomes-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .about-hero {
      padding-block: 42px 50px;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: clamp(2.35rem, 11vw, 3rem);
    }

    .hero-actions {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .hero-actions :global(.button) {
      width: 100%;
    }

    .hero-note {
      border-left: 0;
      border-top: 3px solid var(--color-lbs-red);
      gap: 12px;
      padding-left: 0;
      padding-top: 16px;
    }

    .hero-note ol {
      gap: 10px 14px;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .hero-note li {
      font-size: 0.92rem;
    }

    .thesis-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .rule {
      height: 4px;
      min-height: 0;
      width: 58px;
    }

    dl {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    dl div,
    dl div:first-child {
      border-left: 0;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      padding: 16px 0;
    }

    dl div:first-child {
      border-top: 0;
    }

    .process-list article {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
